x4freetext: The 5.5 MeV H.V.E.C. Van de Graaff
accelerator was used.
Two ORTEC solid state detectors operated at
200 V bias were used to detect the reaction products.
These detectors were placed at 90 and 150 degr.,
respectively, with respect to the beam direction.
Thin self-supporting 27Al targets (3 keV for 2 MeV
protons) were used.
The absolute error of the cross section
The relative error between various
excitation functions and from point to point is
estimated to be no more than + - 5%, except at very low
cross sections when the statistical error becomes
predominantly large.
